title: Contributing to GeoPressureR
text: Fork package clone onto computer. haven’t done , recommend using usethis::create_from_github("Rafnuss/GeoPressureR", fork = TRUE). Install development dependencies devtools::install_dev_deps(), make sure package passes R CMD check running devtools::check(). R CMD check doesn’t pass cleanly, ’s good idea ask help continuing. Create Git branch pull request (PR). recommend using usethis::pr_init("brief-description--change"). Make changes, commit git, create PR running usethis::pr_push(), following prompts browser. title PR briefly describe change. body PR contain Fixes #issue-number. user-facing changes, add bullet top NEWS.md (.e. just first header). Follow style described https://style.tidyverse.org/news.html.

what: Retrieve ERA5 variable along edge — edge_add_wind
title: Retrieve ERA5 variable along edge — edge_add_wind
text: Reads NetCDF files extract variable requested along flight defined edges. Time: linear interpolation using resolution requested rounding_interval Space: nearest neighbour interpolation default bi-linear pracma::interp2 interp_spatial_linear=TRUE Pressure/altitude: linear interpolation using exact pressure values

title: Retrieve ERA5 variable along edge — edge_add_wind
code: edge_add_wind(   tag_graph,   edge_s,   edge_t,   pressure = NULL,   variable = c("u", "v"),   rounding_interval = 60,   interp_spatial_linear = FALSE,   return_averaged_variable = FALSE,   file = function(stap_id)     glue::glue("./data/wind/{tag_graph$param$id}/{tag_graph$param$id}_{stap_id}.nc"),   quiet = FALSE )

title: Retrieve ERA5 variable along edge — edge_add_wind
text: tag_graph either tag graph GeoPressureR object. edge_s index source node edge. Either vector 3D index matrix 3 columns, one dimension. edge_t index target node edge. Either vector 3D index matrix 3 columns, one dimension. pressure pressure measurement associated tag data used estimate pressure level (.e., altitude) bird flights. data.frame needs contain date POSIXt value hPa. variable list variables extract ERA5 pressure level  using shortName notation: "u", "v",  "t", "cc", "r", "w", "ciwc", "clwc", "q", "cswc", "d", "z", "o3", "pv", 'vo". rounding_interval temporal resolution query variable (min). Default match ERA5 native resolution (1hr). interp_spatial_linear logical interpolate variable linearly space, FALSE takes nearest neighbour. ERA5 native resolution 0.25° return_averaged_variable logical return variable timestep average entire flight. file absolute relative path ERA5 wind data file downloaded. Function taking single argument stationary period identifier. quiet logical hide messages progress

title: Compute likelihood map from pressure data — geopressure_map
text: geopressure_map_mismatch() computes mismatch maps Google Earth Engine via map entry point GeoPressure API. consists following steps: Pre-process pressure: pressure measurements first smoothed downscaled 1-hour resolution order match ERA-5 resolution (see geopressure_map_preprocess()). Generate requests: Send single request GeoPressureAPI generate Google Earth Engine (GEE) URLs, one elevation/stationary period can used compute maps GEE server. Send requests: Call URLs, start computation GEE server. step, wait answer, send requests parallel faster. Compute download maps: requests sent, wait GEE server return geotiff file (map) elevation/ stationary period. Post-process maps: Read geotiff maps matrix, create corresponding GeoPressureR map object create_map(). following two maps returned stationary period: map_pressure_mse: Mean Square Error (MSE) data logger pressure time series reanalysis. mean error removed assume specific altitude geolocator, thus allowing altitudinal shift pressure time series. map_pressure_mask (optionally): mask proportion pressure measurements corresponding altitude values found within min max ground elevation location. altitude value geolocator pressure time series computed barometric formula accounting temporal variation pressure (surface-pressure) temperature (2m-temperature) based ERA5 data. min max ground elevation pixel computed SRTM-90. map returned keep_mask TRUE. details, read GeoPressure API documentation .

what: Convert mismatch map into likelihood map
title: Compute likelihood map from pressure data — geopressure_map
text: convert map mean square error \(MSE\) altitude mask \(z_{mask}\) computed geopressure_map_mismatch() likelihood map , $$L = \left( \frac{1}{2 \pi \sigma^2}\right)^{\frac{nw}{2}} \exp \left(-w n \frac{MSE}{2\sigma^2} \right) \left[z_{mask}>T \right],$$ \(\sigma\) standard deviation (sd) pressure \(T\) mask threshold (thr_mask). auto-correlation time series accounted equation, use log-linear pooling weight \(w=\log(n)/n\) default, \(n\) number samples time series (.e., data points used compute MSE). See GeoPressureManual | Probability aggregation  details. Important Note: Since GeoPressure v3.1.0, threshold mask happening directly GEE server (.e., geopressure_map_mismatch()). allows compute MSE pixels within threshold, thus reducing computational cost significantly.

what: Request and download pressure time series at a given location — geopressure_timeseries
title: Request and download pressure time series at a given location — geopressure_timeseries
text: function returns surface atmospheric pressure time series ERA5 requested location. location queried water, location moved closest onshore location. ERA5 pressure time series response \(P_{ERA}\) provided hourly basis start_time end_time pressure$date pressure supplied. supply pressure geolocator \(P_{gl}\), function additionally return altitude geolocator sea level \(z_{gl}\) using barometric equation, $$ z_{{gl}}(x)=z_{ERA5}(x) + \frac{T_{ERA5}(x)}{L_b}  \left( \frac{P_{gl}}{P_{ERA5}(x)} \right)^{\frac{RL_b}{g M}-1},$$ \(z_{ERA}\), \(T_{ERA}\), \(P_{ERA}\) respectively correspond ground level elevation, temperature 2m, ground level pressure ERA5, \(L_b\)  standard temperature lapse rate, \(R\) universal gas constant, \(g\) gravity constant  \(M\) molar mass air. See information GeoPressureAPI documentation. able compare temporal variation retrieved pressure ERA5 \(P_{ERA}\) geolocator pressure \(P_{gl}\), function also returns ERA pressure normalized geolocator mean pressure measurement surface_pressure_norm. $$ P_{ERA5,0}(\boldsymbol{x})[t] = \left( P_{ERA5}(\boldsymbol{x})[t]-P_{gl}[t]\right) - \left( \frac{1}{n}\sum_{=1}^{n} P_{ERA5}(\boldsymbol{x})[]-P_{gl}[] \right).$$

title: Workflow for GeoPressureR — geopressuretemplate
text: geopressuretemplate() function manages complete workflow modelling bird trajectories using geolocator data. includes creation tag object, construction likelihood maps (pressure /light), creation graph model construction, , finally, estimation trajectory products pressure path computation. Read Workflow chapter GeoPressureManual  information. able run successfully function, need correctly set-data configuration files according following GeoPressureTemplate standard .

title: Workflow for GeoPressureR — geopressuretemplate
text: geopressuretemplate function high-level entry point coordinates multiple steps processing geolocator data produce trajectories. relies underlying child functions step: Tag Creation geopressuretemplate_tag(): Initializes labels tag object. also generates light pressure likelihood maps: tag_create(): Initializes tag object. tag_label(): Adds labels. tag_set_map(): Sets spatial temporal parameters. "map_pressure" config$geopressuretemplate$likelihood: geopressure_map(): Computes pressure likelihood. "map_light" config$geopressuretemplate$likelihood: twilight_create() |> twilight_read() |> geolight_map(): Computes light likelihood. Graph Creation geopressuretemplate_graph(): Builds movement model graph based tag data, can include wind effects specified. Outputs marginal distributions, likely paths, simulation paths can computed. graph_create(): Creates graph based tag. config$graph_set_movement$type == "gs" (.e., wind): graph_set_movement(): Sets movement model without wind. config$graph_set_movement$type == "" (.e., wind): graph_add_wind(): Adds wind data graph. graph_set_movement(): Sets movement model wind. "marginal" config$geopressuretemplate$outputs: graph_marginal(): Computes marginal distribution map. "most_likely" config$geopressuretemplate$outputs: graph_most_likely(): Computes likely path based movement model. "simulation" config$geopressuretemplate$outputs: graph_simulation(): Runs simulations model multiple possible paths. path_geopressureviz_{id}.csv exists ./data/interim/: Save data.frame variable path_geopressureviz (see ) save(): Saves computed graph associated objects data/interim/{id}.Rdata Pressure Path Processing geopressuretemplate_pressurepath(): Computes pressurepaths (pressurepath_create) using content Rdata file appending pressurepath data.frame file. "most_likely" config$geopressuretemplate$pressurepath, computes pressure path path_most_likely. "geopressureviz" config$geopressuretemplate$pressurepath computes pressure path path_geopressureviz child functions can called individually automatically part geopressuretemplate workflow.

Usually, either geosphere::distHaversine (fast) geosphere::distGeo (precise slow). See https://rspatial.org/raster/sphere/2-distance.html options details. geosphere_bearing function compute bearing. Either geosphere::bearing (default) geosphere::bearingRhumb. See https://rspatial.org/raster/sphere/3-direction.html#bearing details. workers number workers used computation edges ground speed. workers (limit future::availableCores()) usually makes computation faster, number edges large, memory often limit computation. quiet logical hide messages progress.

title: Create a tag object — tag_create
text: id unique identifier tag. manufacturer One NULL, "soi", "migratetech", "bas", "lund", "prestag", "datapackage" "dataframe". crop_start remove data date (POSIXct character UTC). crop_end remove data date (POSIXct character UTC). directory path directory tag files can read. pressure_file name file pressure data. Full pathname  finishing extensions (e.g., "*.pressure", "*.deg" "*_press.xlsx"). light_file name file light data. Full pathname  finishing extensions (e.g., "*.glf", "*.lux" "*_acc.xlsx"). acceleration_file name file acceleration data. Full pathname  finishing extensions (e.g., "*.acceleration", "*.deg" "*_acc.xlsx"). temperature_external_file name file temperature data. Full pathname  finishing extensions (e.g., "*.temperature", "*.airtemperature" "*.deg"). External air temperature generally temperature sensor directed outward bird. temperature_internal_file name file temperature data . Full pathname  finishing extensions (e.g., "*.bodytemperature"). Internal body temperature generally temperature sensor directed inward (bird tag). magnetic_file name file magnetic/accelerometer data. Full pathname  finishing extensions (e.g., "*.magnetic"). assert_pressure logical check return tag pressure data. quiet logical hide messages progress.

title: Create a tag object — tag_create
text: GeoPressureR tag object containing param parameter object (see param_create()) pressure data.frame columns: date value light (optional) structure pressure temperature_external (optional) structure pressure temperature_internal (optional) structure pressure acceleration (optional) data.frame columns: date, value, act pit. value activity computed sum difference acceleration z-axis (.e. jiggle). SOI sensor, summarised 32 measurements 10Hz pitch relative position bird’s body relative z axis. SOI sensor, average 32 measurements 10Hz. magnetic (optional) data.frame columns: date, magnetic_x, magnetic_y, magnetic_z , acceleration_x, acceleration_y acceleration_z

title: Create a tag object — tag_create
text: current implementation can read files following three sources: GeoLocator Data Package (gldp) pressure_file = "pressure.csv"(optional) light_file = "light.csv" (optional) acceleration_file = "acceleration.csv" (optional) temperature_external_file = "temperature.csv" (optional) temperature_external_file = "airtemperature.csv" (optional) magnetic_file = "magnetic.csv" (optional) Swiss Ornithological Institute (soi) pressure_file = "*.pressure" light_file = "*.glf" (optional) acceleration_file = "*.acceleration" (optional) temperature = "*.temperature" (optional) airtemperature = "*.airtemperature" (optional) magnetic = "*.magnetic" (optional) Migrate Technology (migratetech): pressure_file = "*.deg" light_file = "*.lux" (optional) acceleration_file = "*.deg" (optional) British Antarctic Survey (bas), aquired Biotrack Ltd 2011, renamed Lotek 2019 . works light data (assert_pressure = FALSE) light_file = "*.lig" Lund CAnMove (lund) pressure_file = "*_press.xlsx" light_file = "*_acc.xlsx" (optional) acceleration_file = "*_acc.xlsx" (optional) BitTag/PresTag (prestag) pressure_file = "*.txt" can also enter data manually (manufacturer = "dataframe") providing data.frame: pressure_file: data.frame columns date value. light_file: (optional) data.frame columns date value. acceleration_file: (optional) data.frame columns date value. temperature_external_file: (optional) data.frame columns date value. temperature_internal_file: (optional) data.frame columns date value. magnetic_file: (optional) data.frame columns date, magnetic_x, magnetic_y, magnetic_z, acceleration_x, acceleration_y acceleration_z. can still create tag without pressure data using assert_pressure = TRUE. tag able run traditional GeoPressureR workflow, can still analysis. default manufacturer = NULL, manufacturer determined automatically content directory. can also specify manually file full pathname file extension using regex expression (e.g., "*.pressure" matches file ending pressure). Please create issue Github data format yet supported. function can used crop data specific date, instance remove pre-equipment post-retrieval data.

title: Automatic labelling acceleration data of a tag — tag_label_auto
text: function uses acceleration data classify migratory flights. function uses k=2 mean clustering (kmeans()) identify high activity periods. Periods high activity lasting min_duration considered migratory flight.

title: Automatic labelling acceleration data of a tag — tag_label_auto
text: tag GeoPressure tag object. min_duration Minimal duration (minutes) consider high activity migratory flight. thr_reclassify Post-processing threshold activity considered re-classification. Typically 0 0.5 (effect). See post-processing details. post_proc_window Post-processing windows considered re-classification. Typically 0 (effect) 5 unit temporal resolution. See post-processing details.

title: Automatic labelling acceleration data of a tag — tag_label_auto

title: Automatic labelling acceleration data of a tag — tag_label_auto
text: Additionally, perform post-processing step improve classification low-activity period happening migration flight (e.g. gliding phase): Mid-activity surrounded flights. kmeans classification classify high-activity values 50% distance two clusters. , classify mid-activity non-flight activity data value greater thr_reclassify distance two kmeans clusters. periods mid-activity surrounded flight also considered flights. avoid stap lasting datapoints, also classify datapoint surrounded flight , within window +/- post_proc_window points. result, stap shorter (2 * post_proc_window + 1) * dt. function inspired function classify_flap PAMlr package.

what: Configure the spatial and temporal parameters of the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
title: Configure the spatial and temporal parameters of the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
text: function adds tag parameters defining 3D grid map. spatial parameters (extent scale) define geographical dimensions map, temporal dimension defined based stationary periods built using labels. include_stap_id include_min_duration can used limit stationary periods computed modelled analysis. default, stationary periods included. addition, tag offers possibility define known locations (e.g., equipment retrieval site). can defined level stationary period (.e., assuming constant position whole stationary period) can define many known stationary periods wish. index last stationary period generally unknown, can use negative indexing known, .e., known$stap_id = -1 converted nrow(tag$stap). default, likelihood map computed stationary periods trajectory model constrained, saving significant computational time. can change using compute_known parameter geopressure_map().

code: tag_set_map(   tag,   extent,   scale = 10,   known = data.frame(stap_id = integer(), known_lat = double(), known_lon = double()),   include_stap_id = NULL,   include_min_duration = 0 )

title: Configure the spatial and temporal parameters of the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
text: tag GeoPressureR tag object. extent geographical extent map likelihood graph model computed. Vector length 4 c(xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax) c(W, E, S, N). scale number pixels per 1° latitude-longitude. instance, scale = 10 resolution 0.1° (~10km) scale=4 resolution 0.25° (~30km). avoid interpolating ERA5 data, scale equal smaller 10. Read scale Google earth Engine documentation . known data.frame containing known positions bird (e.g., equipment retrieval site) columns stap_id, known_lat known_lon. can set position last stationary period using stap_id = -1. Also accept list converted data.frame. include_stap_id vector stap_id defining stationary period model, , compute likelihood map use graph. include_min_duration minimum duration threshold stationary periods include (hours).

what: Compute wind support and drift from a wind and ground speed vectors — windsupport
title: Compute wind support and drift from a wind and ground speed vectors — windsupport
text: Wind support, wind profit, projection wind vector \(\vec{v}_w\) onto groundspeed vector \(\vec{v}_g\), $$\text{Wind Support} = \frac{\vec{v}_g \cdot \vec{v}_w}{|\vec{v}_g|}$$, \(\cdot\) cross product. positive value indicates wind blowing direction movement, negative one indicates head wind. windspeed groundspeed expressed complex value real part corresponds east-west component imaginary part north-south component. Alternatively wind support, can compute drift (crosswind component) value drift = TRUE, $$\text{Drift} = \frac{|\vec{v}_g \times \vec{v}_w|}{|\vec{v}_g|}$$, \(\times\) cross product. positive value drift indicates wind pushing bird right intended path, negative indicates wind pushing bird left. can use abs() (Mod()) compute norm (absolute value) speed vector speed_to_bearing() compute bearing/orientation speed vector. latter computes trigonometric angle speed vector Arg() convert angle bearing (North = 0° instead 90°).

title: Compute wind support and drift from a wind and ground speed vectors — windsupport
